    "question_id" : 9102318,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Indeed, the simplest way is to use <code>intValue()</code>. However, this merely returns the integer part; it does not do any rounding. If you want the Integer <em>nearest</em> to the Double value, you'll need to do this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer integer = Integer.valueOf((int) Math.round(myDouble)));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And don't forget the null case:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer integer = myDouble == null ? null : Integer.valueOf((int) Math.round(myDouble)));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>Math.round()</code> handles odd duck cases, like infinity and NaN, with relative grace.</p>\n"
  }, {
